exercises.name: Walking
exercises.guide:
A nice gentle walk building up to good pace.

You should aim to be 3 on the borg scale. 

Your heart rate should not exceed 120 bpm and your oxygen should not fall below 88 (Except for patients with pulmanory fibrosis)

If you have known heart problems then you must not stop at the end of this timer and should move slowly between excercises.

exercises.name: Marching
exercises.guide:
A nice brisk March.

You should aim to be 4 on the borg scale. 

Your heart rate should not exceed 120 bpm and your oxygen should not fall below 88 (Except for patients with pulmanory fibrosis)

If you have known heart problems then you must not stop at the end of this timer and should move slowly between excercises.
